CatDescriptText: Mr. Delano Latney, night watchman, 217 Dinwiddie Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the visit of the Russian ruler, Khrushchev, will promote world peace?" answer reads: "No, I wouldn't say that it will promote peace, but I do believe that it might lead to a better relationship."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Delano Latney wearing moustache, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade with Bud Saunders Flowers, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
